Given an integer N and flag isReturnEven
a:- If isReturnEven is true then return the sum of even positions digits of integer N.
b:- If isReturnEven is false then return the sum of odd position digits of integer N.

position of digits start from the left with 1 as the position. Refer to the below example
If n=25674, 
then:-
Position 1 is 2
Position 2 is 5
:
:
:
Position 5 is 4

Input N=43125 isReturnEven=true
Output:- 5 (Digits at even position 3 and 2, So their sum is 5)

Codes Are:-

int fun(int n,int bool isReturnEven)
{
    string s=tostring(n);
    int result=0;
    if(value)
    {
        for(auto i=1;i<s.size();i+=2)
        {
            result+=s[i]-'0';
        }
    }
    else
    {
        for(auto i=0;i<s.size();i+=2)
        {
            result+=s[i]-'0';
        }
    }
    
    return result;
}
